'''''In Their Boots''''' is a [[documentary]] series about the impact the [[War in Iraq]] and the [[War in Afghanistan (2001–present)|War in Afghanistan]] are having on people at home in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2008/07/04/DDAJ11JQR1.DTL | work=The San Francisco Chronicle | title=Webcasts focus on military families' lives | first=Jia-Rui | last=Chong | date=July 5, 2008}}</ref> Every episode features a documentary about how the servicemen and women of the American armed forces, their families, and American communities have been changed by the nation's campaigns in Iraq and Afghanistan.<ref>{{Cite news|title= Marine widow needs act of Congress to let her, son stay in States |url= http://www.stripes.com/news/marine-widow-needs-act-of-congress-to-let-her-son-stay-in-states-1.95147 |publisher=[[Stars and Stripes (newspaper)|Stars and Stripes]]|date=September 30, 2009|first=Allen|last=David}}</ref> The show has covered issues such as the effects of deployment, [[post-traumatic stress disorder]], [[traumatic brain injury]], recovery from physical injury, military widows,<ref>[[The American Widow Project]]</ref> partners of [[gays in the military]],<ref>{{Cite news|title='Silent partner' examines what happens when people 'don't tell'|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/local/la-me-gay-military18-2009jul18,0,848628.story|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=July 18, 2009|first=Alexandra|last=Zavis}}</ref> [[homelessness]], [[women in the military]], and sexual assault in the military. In 2010, In Their Boots launched [[Operation In Their Boots]], which gave 5 combat veterans the opportunity to produce and direct their own documentaries.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Vet Filmmakers Recount War Experiences On-Screen|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=130272420|publisher=[[NPR]]|date=October 1, 2010|first=Gloria|last=Hillard}}</ref>

''In Their Boots'' is funded by a grant from the Iraq Afghanistan Deployment Impact Fund (IADIF) of the [[California Community Foundation]] and is produced by [[Brave New Foundation]].<ref>[http://www.calfund.org/learn/iadifgrants.php?PHPSESSID=5ed63e5d4e9e2f802a434908809e449f "Iraq Afghanistan Deployment Impact Fund Grants"]. Retrieved July 11, 2009</ref>

Season 2 of In their Boots began airing on [[PBS]] stations in July 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|title= Veterans tell war stories on film |url= http://www.vcstar.com/news/2010/jul/03/veterans-tell-war-stories-on-film/ |publisher=[[Ventura County Star]]|date=July 3, 2010|first=Scott|last=Hadly}}</ref>

