{{Refimprove|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox magazine | title = TV Park | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file: prefix --> | image_size = <!-- (defaults to user thumbnail size if no size is stated) --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = Ksenia Dmitriyeva<ref name="about">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-park.ru/index.php?option%3Dcom_content%26view%3Darticle%26id%3D394%26Itemid%3D523 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=December 24, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308025445/http://www.tv-park.ru/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=394&Itemid=523 |archivedate=March 8, 2012 }}</ref> | editor_title = [[Editor-in-chief]] | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = entertainment industry news | frequency = weekly | circulation = 350,000 | publisher = Media Park | founder = Nikolay Chernonog | founded = | firstdate = 1994 | company = | country = Russia | based = [[Moscow]]<ref name="about"/> | language = Russian | website = {{URL|www.tv-park.ru}} | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''TV Park''''' ({{lang-ru|ТВ Парк}}) is a Russian weekly television [[listings magazine]], published by Media Park. As well as programme details, the publication also features articles on current TV events, films, sports news, music, a [[horoscope]], and such regular [[Column (periodical)|columns]] as ''Person of the Week'', ''Photo Project'', ''Personal Life'', ''Dynasty'', and ''Mysteries''.
The first issue of the magazine was released in March 1994, making it the first Russian TV listings magazine. Targeted at "[[middle class|the middle class]]", ''TV Park'' is one of Russia's leading weeklies: as of 2010, it was the 3rd most popular magazine in [[Moscow]], 10th in [[Saint Petersburg]], and nationally in 9th place overall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media-atlas.ru/items/?id=15184&cat=companynews|script-title=ru:Изменения в журнале «ТВ парк»|publisher=Media Atlas|language=Russian|accessdate=24 December 2011}}</ref>
The magazine was founded by, and belongs to, the [[general director]] of Media Park, Nikolay Chernogog.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tefi.ru/ru/art/ART-biograf/index.php?&id14=149&i14=268|script-title=ru:Состав АРТ-биографии :: Черноног Николай Андреевич|publisher=[[TEFI]]|language=Russian|accessdate=24 December 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122015418/http://www.tefi.ru/ru/art/ART-biograf/index.php|archivedate=22 January 2012|df=}}</ref> ''TV Park'' is the official sponsor of the [[TEFI]] television award.
